SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 167
BY SENATOR BARROW
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH. Recognizes Friday, May 29, 2026, as Youth Legislature
of Louisiana Day at the Louisiana State Capitol.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To recognize Friday, May 29, 2026, as Youth Legislature of Louisiana Day at the Louisiana
3 State Capitol and to commend Youth Legislature of Louisiana for its longstanding
4 commitment to civic education, leadership development, and student engagement in
5 the legislative process and to recognize its transformative impact on young leaders
6 throughout the state of Louisiana.
7 WHEREAS, Youth Legislature of Louisiana is an educational program dedicated to
8 inspiring and empowering future generations of leaders through civic engagement and
9 experiential learning; and
10 WHEREAS, founded in 1978, Youth Legislature of Louisiana has been shaped by
11 decades of passionate students, educators, mentors, and civic leaders, providing an
12 opportunity for young people to foster and develop skills to experience the responsibilities
13 of lawmakers, engage in critical analysis of public policy, and influence meaningful change
14 for the betterment of the state; and
15 WHEREAS, the program has established itself as an innovative and highly respected
16 model for civic education, cultivating informed, engaged, and confident young citizens
17 equipped to participate actively in the democratic process; and
18 WHEREAS, each year, more than one thousand eight hundred middle school
