1 students representing diverse educational settings across approximately fifteen parishes
2 participate in mock legislative sessions held at the historic Old State Capitol in Baton Rouge
3 serving as legislators, committee chairs, members of the media, and executive branch
4 officials, thereby gaining firsthand knowledge of the legislative process and the
5 responsibilities of public service; and
6 WHEREAS, by simulating the legislative process, the program deepens civic
7 engagement and understanding, enabling students to learn how laws are created and
8 demonstrating the profound impact their voices can have within their communities and
9 across the state; and
10 WHEREAS, Youth Legislature of Louisiana further strengthens critical thinking by
11 encouraging participants to analyze real-world issues, evaluate competing viewpoints, and
12 develop persuasive, solution-oriented proposals; and
13 WHEREAS, students participating in the program develop confidence and
14 proficiency in public speaking as they learn to present ideas effectively, advocate for
15 legislation, and communicate with clarity and conviction; and
16 WHEREAS, through hands-on education and meaningful collaboration, students not
17 only gain a greater appreciation for government and public service but also build lasting
18 relationships, strengthen their sense of civic responsibility, and discover their own potential
19 to shape the future of Louisiana.
20 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
21 does hereby recognize Friday, May 29, 2026, as Youth Legislature of Louisiana Day at the
22 Louisiana State Capitol, does hereby commend Youth Legislature of Louisiana for its
23 extraordinary contributions to civic education and youth leadership development, and does
24 hereby recognize its enduring impact in preparing future generations of engaged and
25 informed citizens.
26 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
27 Cheryle Totten, Founder and Executive Director of the Youth Legislature of Louisiana.
